of females were given in 
<bibRefCitation author="Karimpour, Y. &amp; Tavakoli, M. &amp; Melika, G." box="[805,1238,1328,1354]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" pagination="16 - 32" refId="ref12883" refString="Karimpour, Y., Tavakoli, M. &amp; Melika, G. (2008) New species of herb gallwasps from the Middle East (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae, Aylacini). Zootaxa, 1854 (1) -, 16 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1854.1.2" type="journal article" year="2008">Karimpour, Tavakoli &amp; Melika (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Here we provide colour plates for females (
<figureCitation box="[445,574,1364,1390]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1414,1438]" captionTargetBox="[198,1384,200,1378]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[188,1397,181,1390]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 64–69. Isocolus beheni Melika &amp; Karimpour, 2008, female. 64–67, head: 64, frontal view, 65, dorsal view, 66, posterior view, 67, lateral view; 68, antenna, 69, pronotum and mesoscutum, anterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683318" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683318/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs 64–69</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[586,658,1364,1391]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 76–79" captionStart-1="FIGURES 80–84" captionStartId-0="19.[151,264,1607,1631]" captionStartId-1="20.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox-0="[171,1421,203,1570]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1433,435,1826]" captionTargetId-0="figure-18@19.[151,1436,181,1583]" captionTargetId-1="figure-134@20.[151,1436,417,1830]" captionTargetPageId-0="19" captionTargetPageId-1="20" captionText-0="FIGURES 76–79. Isocolus beheni Melika &amp; Karimpour, 2008, female. 76–77, mesosoma: 76, lateral view, 77, frontal view, 78–79, mesoscutum and mesoscutellum, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 80–84. Isocolus beheni Melika &amp; Karimpour, 2008. 80–82, female: 80, forewing, 81, metascutellum and propodeum, posterodorsal view, 82, metasoma, lateral view. 83–84, infested flowerheads: 83, young, growing and mature, dried, 84, dried, with wasp emergence hole." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683322" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683324" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6683322/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6683324/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">76–82</figureCitation>
) for easier identification. Males (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1161,1364,1391]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,608,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-207@18.[151,1436,597,1887]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Isocolus beheni Melika &amp; Karimpour, 2008, male. 70–73, head: 70, frontal view, 71, dorsal view, 72, posterior view, 73, lateral view; 74, antenna; 75, metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683320" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683320/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs 70–75</figureCitation>
) were found for the first time which are similar to females but the antenna as long as body, dark brown to black, with 12 flagellomeres, the pedicel only slightly longer than broad, F1 straight, apically not swollen, shorter than F2, F2=F3 and longer than F1, F2 till F 11 nearly equal in length, F12 1.6× as long as F11, placodeal sensilla indistinct, on F1–F12. Body length 
<quantity box="[151,286,1508,1535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" unit="mm" value="3.55" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.9 mm</quantity>
(n = 7).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,932,2039]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,250,1544,1570]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Gall</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[267,399,1544,1571]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 80–84" captionStart-1="FIGURE 85" captionStartId-0="20.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionStartId-1="21.[151,250,1620,1644]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1433,435,1826]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,181,1597]" captionTargetId-0="figure-134@20.[151,1436,417,1830]" captionTargetId-1="figure-18@21.[151,1436,181,1597]" captionTargetPageId-0="20" captionTargetPageId-1="21" captionText-0="FIGURES 80–84. Isocolus beheni Melika &amp; Karimpour, 2008. 80–82, female: 80, forewing, 81, metascutellum and propodeum, posterodorsal view, 82, metasoma, lateral view. 83–84, infested flowerheads: 83, young, growing and mature, dried, 84, dried, with wasp emergence hole." captionText-1="FIGURE 85. Isocolus beheni Melika &amp; Karimpour, 2008. Infested flowerheads of Centaurea sp." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683324" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683328" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6683324/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6683328/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs 83–85</figureCitation>
). Galls are cryptic chambers inside flowerheads that cause no visible external deformation. Usually more than one larval chamber is present in a single flowerhead.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,932,2039]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1616,1642]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Biology.</emphasis>
Galls mature by the end of spring and early summer; adults emerge from June-August through to February of the following year. Host plants are 
<taxonomicName box="[704,965,1652,1678]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ammoyanus">
<emphasis box="[704,965,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Centaurea ammoyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.), 
<taxonomicName box="[1034,1136,1652,1678]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="behen">
<emphasis box="[1034,1136,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. behen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authority="(DC.) Hand." authorityName="Hand." baseAuthorityName="DC." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bruguierana">
<emphasis box="[1187,1362,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. bruguierana</emphasis>
(DC.) Hand.
</taxonomicName>
-Mazz. (
<taxonomicName box="[312,442,1688,1714]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,932,2039]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1724,1750]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Distribution.</emphasis>
Aligudarz-Khakbetieh, Aligudarz-Ab Sefid Waterfall, Khak-be Tiahe, Khorramabad-Tafe Nozhian, 
<collectingRegion box="[225,431,1760,1787]" country="Iran" name="Lorestan" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Lorestan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[441,490,1761,1787]" name="Iran" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Previously recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[757,802,1761,1787]" name="Iran" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Iran</collectingCountry>
also from Urmia, 
<collectingRegion box="[1004,1293,1760,1787]" country="Iran" name="Azarbayjan-e Gharbi" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">West Azarbaijan Province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Karimpour, Y. &amp; Tavakoli, M. &amp; Melika, G." pageId="16" pageNumber="317" pagination="16 - 32" refId="ref12883" refString="Karimpour, Y., Tavakoli, M. &amp; Melika, G. (2008) New species of herb gallwasps from the Middle East (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae, Aylacini). Zootaxa, 1854 (1) -, 16 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1854.1.2" type="journal article" year="2008">Karimpour, Tavakoli &amp; Melika 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,932,2039]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1832,1858]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Comments.</emphasis>
The galls of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melika &amp; Karimpour" authorityYear="2008" box="[493,594,1832,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Isocolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beheni">
<emphasis box="[493,594,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">I. beheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pujade-Villar, 2014" authorityName="Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2014" box="[816,1158,1832,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Isocolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melikai">
<emphasis box="[816,924,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">I. melikai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Tormos, J. &amp; Gonzalez-Nunez, M. &amp; Pascual, S. &amp; Cobo, A." box="[934,1158,1832,1858]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" pagination="41 - 52" refId="ref14490" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Tormos, J., Gonzalez-Nunez, M., Pascual, S. &amp; Cobo, A. (2014) First report of bivoltinism in Isocolus (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae): Isocolus melikai Pujade-Villar n. sp. from the Iberian Peninsula. Zoosystema, 36 (1), 41 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2014 n 1 a 3" type="journal article" year="2014">Pujade-Villar, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the wasps are morphologically different. The lower face of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melika &amp; Karimpour" authorityYear="2008" box="[616,715,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Isocolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beheni">
<emphasis box="[616,715,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">I. beheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reticulate, the clypeus ventrally is rounded, without a median incision, the mesoscutum with some transverse rugae, the median mesoscutal line present, the 2nd metasomal tergum completely micropunctured while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2014" box="[629,735,1940,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Isocolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melikai">
<emphasis box="[629,735,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">I. melikai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lower face is delicately coriaceous, the clypeus is incised ventrally, the mesoscutum strongly rugose, without median mesoscutal line, the 2nd metasomal tergum with micropuncture only in the posterior half (Pujade- Villar 
<emphasis box="[712,761,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">et al</emphasis>
. 2014).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
